title: View a Daily Dispatch
content:
Any charges reported in these press releases are merely accusations and the defendants are presumed innocent unless and until proven guilty.
AK16055956
Dispatch Text:
On 07/30/2016 at approximately 0223 hours, Alaska State Troopers responded to a residence on N. Pioneer Peak Drive in Wasilla for a reported suicide. Investigation revealed a juvenile male age 14 of Wasilla was located in his bedroom and had a self-inflicted gunshot wound to his head. He was pronounced deceased on scene and his remains were released to the State Medical Examiner's Office. The next of kin were notified and no foul play is suspected.
